Teaching

   The Paris observatory proposes courses in astronomy, astrophysics and
   space technology at all levels of higher education: university degrees
   (diplômes d’université), master, Ph.D. It also provides continued
   education for numerous teachers.

Department of Education (UFE)

     * Director : Guillaume Aulanier
     * Deputy director : Noël Robichon
     * Assistant to the director : Nicole Romain

Personel (déc 2014)

     * 11 technical and administrative (8 staff + 3 contractors)
     * 83 staff teaching researchers (8 from cnu + 75 from cnap)
     * 26 temporary teaching researchers (4 teaching postdocs + 22
       teaching PhDs)
     * 6 attached teachers and researchers

Training policy

Registry

